Introduction
============
    Do basic power management testing including ACPI, Tickless etc.

Build and Run
=============
    Build the tests:
 	cd mcts-3dgfx-tests
	./pack.sh    -- create a rpm package: power-tests-xx.rpm
	rpm -ivh power-tests-xx.rpm		--install the test package
	or make / make install
	The cases would be installed in /opt/power-tests/
    Run the tests
	You can run the scripts directly or from web UI.
    Test Environment
	Hardware requirements: handset and netbook
	Software requirements: X process must be working, and you have to set DISPLAY env variant when you test from a remote end. For example: export DISPLAY=:0.0

Common Install
==============
    ./autogen
    ./configure prefix=/usr
    make && make install

